article.headline: Wright St. 67, Green Bay 54
article.story: CLEVELAND -- Vaughn Duggins scored 20 points and Wright State defeated Wisconsin-Green Bay 67-54 on Saturday night. N'Gai Evans added 18 points and Todd Brown had 17 for the Raiders (17-9, 10-5 Horizon League), who have won six of their past seven games and improved to 11-1 at home. Leading 28-27 at halftime, the Raiders broke open the game with a 12-3 run in the second half. A 3-pointer by Brown capped the run to give the Raiders a 45-35 lead with 13:35 remaining. the Phoenix would get no closer than five points the rest of the way. Hot shooting in the second half -- the Raiders made 15 of 24 (62.5 percent) -- kept the Phoenix at bay. The Raiders made 27 of 53 field goal attempts for the game (50.9 percent). Rahmon Fletcher scored 14 points and Bryquis Perine added 11 for the Phoenix (17-9, 9-6), who had a two-game winning streak snapped.
